                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (182), switch on right turn signal, and measure voltage from circuit
                                57DS to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(182), 57DS to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Pulsating 12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 57DS and 57D from turn signal switch,
                                then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (182), and at (J7)/(181) circuit 57H, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(181), 57H to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Pulsating 12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 57H, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (182), switch on left turn signal, and measure voltage from circuit
                                56DS to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(182), 56DS to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
