                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (182), place transmission in reverse and move key switch to ignition
                                position. Measure voltage from circuit 71B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(182), 71B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 71B from back-up light switch, then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (182), and at (J7)/(181) circuit 71C, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(181), 71C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
