                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check fuse F15 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F15</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move key switch to ACC. position. At fuse F15 and circuit 12A, measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
