                            <para>Go to Step 6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in blue wire from fuse F15, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>20.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove fuse F10 and check for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F10</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At fuse F10 and circuit 14B, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F10, 14B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14B or 14P, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>22.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace fuse F10, and at (J7)/(181) terminal 8, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(181), term. 8 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in brown or green wire from fuse F10, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>23.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove relay (179), and at circuit 12F, measure voltage to ground.</para>
