                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 12E, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>27.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance in circuit 12E to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(179), 12E to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition in circuit 12E, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
